# PROJECT 4

**Name**: Marco Preciado
**Date**: Wed Feb 25 09:13:33 PM CST 2026
**Environment**: Ubuntu on Windows ,VSCode, Penguin Linux/GNU, VIM
**Purpose**: Simulate the round robin scheduler on an OSS

## How to compile the project:

Reset project just in case:

```bash
make clean
```

Then recompile project:

```bash
make clean
```

## Usage

```bash
./oss -n INTEGER -s INTEGER -t DECIMAL -i DECIMAL
```

## Arguments

```bash
./oss [-h] [-n proc] [-s simul] [-t childTimeLimit] [-i launchTimeLimit] [-f logfile]
```

-h: prints help message
-n proc: number of maximum processes oss will launch overal including simul.
-s simul: number of simultaneous processes taht oss will launch. Does not exceed [-n proc].
-t childTimeLimit: a bound time limit that children use for time execution
-i launchTimeLimit: a bount time limit that decides when oss should launch a child
-f logfile: the name of the log file that will be printed when the system is running


Example:
```bash
./oss -n 2 -s 1 -t 1 -i 2 -f logfile
```

